This paper discusses an adaptation and application of a search-based structured prediction algorithm to unsupervised learning problems. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as unsupervised shift-reduce parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of supervised learning in unsupervised learning problems also relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in both machine learning and natural language processing. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the predict-self idea, which is a technique used in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS).
